It's hard for me to understand the outrage over the Suicide Forest video. I have seen at least 2 other documentaries on the subject and both had shown skeletal remains that hadn't been located or removed as yet. Obviously if there is a video on the subject, the impact of the conundrum can only be felt by showing some of the sites where this occurs. There are plenty of programs that show deceased individuals, however briefly that may be (such as true crime shows or coroner shows).  Also, if a person is mindful of their privacy, they probably wouldn't commit suicide in a public place. And since the particular individual in the video hadn't been identified, how harmful was it to the family? Youtube shows videos of horrendous attacks by animals against humans, humans hunting animals for sport, etc. Why is America getting so judgmental about reality.

Oh nonsense. I have never seen one of the kid's videos, nor this Casey guy. But I'm tired of him, others, and this topic popping up everywhere. 
This kid Logan Paul, typical tasteless, stupid tripe apparently, no interest. However people need to get a backbone. Yes, he went to that park and filmed a dead person. While tasteless, it is not the end of the world!!
He removed it shortly after.Give me a break. People die. Give him a break as well...he's young and learned a valuable lesson hopefully. It is this (lack of) culture today. It must build one's efo to have such a following. This venue promotes it..Look at all the nitwits wanting to be movie stars here after all?!
Should it have been taken down? Not really. One sees the same on documentaries.. In the name of good taste and behavior? Yes, it should have been removed if UTube were my business. Nevertheless, he did so regardless.
There are far worse things done and shown on TV in the USA. Heaven forbid one see a naked body, but there is no problem showing people hacked to pieces.

Furthermore, UTube has right to do what they want as it is their business, their venue.

Lastly, you imbeciles who preach free speech need to understand what it means. One may behave like a buffoon all they wish as long as they are not inciting violence or promoting hate speech. PERIOD.
Learn the power of the boycott. It is America's greatest strength. Don't like it? Don't use it, it WILL go away!
